OL,3,GSouth West
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FA day of sunshine and blustery
OL,6,Fshowers, though the showers tending to
OL,7,Fbecome more isolated and lighter
OL,8,Fduring the afternoon. Feeling pleasant
OL,9,Fin the sun but temperatures a little
OL,10,Fbelow average. Breezy near coasts.
OL,11,
OL,12,CTonight:FShowers becoming less
OL,13,Ffrequent for a time into the evening,
OL,14,Fbefore returning later in the night,
OL,15,Fperhaps merging to give longer spells
OL,16,Fof rain later in the night.
OL,17,
OL,18,CWednesday:FA cloudy start, with
OL,19,Fshowers or longer spells of rain
OL,20,Fduring the morning. Feeling cool for
OL,21,Fthe time of year.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
